LOUISVILLE, Ky (WHAS11) -- If you enjoy music, food and so much more, then you should be heading to the Highview Community Festival and Parade. 
At 11 a.m. this Saturday, you can come out to the Highview neighborhood to celebrate with local residents. There's going to be live music, business booths, bounce rides for the kids and much more. 
The festival will be located at the Outer Loop Plaza near the ValuMarket. The best part about the festival? It is completely free. 
The festival will go on until 4 p.m. Read  //on.whas11.com/1LnwGvP More Stories
